This HTML structure includes the basic elements outlined in the design concept. You'll need to add CSS styles to make it look visually appealing.

Create a separate CSS file (styles.css) and add styles to enhance the layout, typography, and colors. You can use the color scheme and typography guidelines provided earlier.

```
/* styles.css */
body {
    font-family: Open Sans, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

header {
    background-color: #8BC34A;
    color: #FFFFFF;
    padding: 1em;
    text-align: center;
}

.hero {
    background-image: url('fresh-produce.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    color: #FFFFFF;
}

.categories {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
}

.categories ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

.categories li {
    margin: 1em;
}

.products {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
}

.products ul
